  "text": "In Latin-American countries where preeclampsia is one of the leading causes of maternal and fetal mortality [CITATION_1] , information about this disease has been mainly related to what has been studied in developed countries. This means that information about regional particularities of the disease and its consequences in mothers and their children, or even, the relationship to the future cardiovascular disease, is unknown. In this article, information about preeclampsia and endothelial dysfunction drawn from research groups based in Latin-American countries will be highlighted to illustrate the need for increased international and regional collaborations to search for regional particularities regarding vascular dysfunction in mother and offspring during preeclampsia.",
